      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register a New User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "if (json.token) {\r",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"jwt_token\", json.token);\r",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n  \"email\": \"richard@finaltest.com\",\r\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\r\n  \"role\": \"admin\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Registers a new user in the Farm Supply Chain system and securely hashes their password.\n\n### Request Details\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/api/v1/auth/register` (or `/api/auth/register` depending on your setup)\n    \n- **Auth Required:** No\n    \n\n### Request Body\n\nThe request requires a JSON body containing the user's credentials and their designated role within the supply chain (`admin`, `farmer`, `retailer`, or `distributor`).\n\n\\`\\`\\`json  \n{  \n\"email\": \"[richard2@test.com](https://mailto:richard2@test.com)\",  \n\"password\": \"password123\",  \n\"role\": \"admin\"  \n}"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "User Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "\r",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 && json.token) {\r",
                  "    // This saves the token to your environment automatically\r",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"jwt_token\", json.token);\r",
                  "    console.log(\"JWT Token saved! You can now use {{jwt_token}} in other requests.\");\r",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n  \"email\": \"richard@finaltest.com\",\r\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\r\n  \"role\": \"admin\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Authenticates an existing user and returns a JSON Web Token (JWT) required to access protected routes within the Farm Supply Chain API.\n\n### Request Details\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **Endpoint:** `/api/v1/auth/login` (or `/api/auth/login`)\n    \n- **Auth Required:** No\n    \n\n### Request Body\n\nThe request requires the user's registered email and password.\n\n\\`\\`\\`json  \n{  \n\"email\": \"[richard2@test.com](https://mailto:richard2@test.com)\",  \n\"password\": \"password123\"  \n}"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
